				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1929896#post-2694163</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1929896/scp-2462#post-2694163</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 18 Nov 2016 18:57:20 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>AgentWilson</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>802114</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>In the context of botany, human-assisted reproduction is referred to as cultivation rather than breeding. So a specimen is cultivated rather than bred, and a particular variety of a species is called a cultivar rather than a breed. I hope that helps.</p> 
				 	]]>
